The Microsoft billing and CRM solutions provide valuable analytics and reporting tools with real-time visibility into what subscribers are doing on an operator’s network—how services and products are being used and consumed, and which promotions, products, and services are most popular amongst various customer segments, and how many movies or mobile games subscribers purchased.

¬The solutions enable a full suite of order management capabilities, including workflows to manage complex activation ordering, physical installations, equipment reservations and allocations, fault resolutions, technical dispatch, and on-site installations. Order management also enables offline credit checks and facilities confirmations.

Because Microsoft Dynamics CRM is fully integrated into partners’ BSS platform, keeping pace with the constant introduction of new technologies becomes much simpler. This helps operators to future-proof their CRM, potentially saving millions in customisation charges over time and simplifying the CRM desktop by linking all back office systems,  streamlining business data for more accurate, consistent, and agile operations.

A solid and reliable BSS platform is a critical component for every service provider. Microsoft and its partners are experienced, long-standing vendors in the telecommunications industry. By pairing Microsoft’s strengths in CRM technology and usability with partners’ strengths in billing and CRM projects, we have created a world-class product that is greater than the sum of its parts.

The billing and CRM solutions are much more than a customer care solution. They drive value across the entire organisation for groups such as marketing, finance, sales, product management, and networks. They automate business processes, including order management, workflow automation, and contract management, for an end-to-end view of the full customer life cycle.
